{
  "texts": [
    "Given this distribution of term frequencies, a given edge weight value can carry very different information.",
    "An edge weight of 2 could indicate a significant relationship between two terms that occur 5 times each.",
    "Between two terms that occur hundreds of times each, an edge weigh of 2 would be noise.",
    "When we convert the edge weights to NPMI values, they are scaled to the range [-1,+1] and high values are assigned to edges that represent frequent co-occurrence relative to the frequencies of the connected terms.",
    "This distribution resembles a bell curve."
  ]
}